                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/5579: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-04-23T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 23, 1928—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>99. Department’s 98, April 21, 2 p.m. La Luz Company reports receipt of further
                    advices from Bluefields stating that four Americans and Harry J. Amphlett,
                    British subject, Superintendent of the mine, have been captured by bandits who
                    raided the mine. They request that all possible steps be taken for their
                    recovery and safety. Please investigate and request Marine Commandant to do
                    everything possible for their safety. Report by cable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
